  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Calculating Distance Between Two Coordinates</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the distance between the points \(A({@x_1@},{@y_1@})\)  and \(B({@x_2@},{@y_2@})\). 
<br>Give your answer in exact form.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(|AB| = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>

<p>Recall that the distance between two points \(P_1(x_1, y_1)\) and \(P_2(x_2, y_2)\) is given by the formula,</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(|P_1 P_2| = \sqrt{(x_2-x_1)^2+(y_2-y_1)^2}\)</p>

<p>In this case, we have,</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(A({@x_1@},{@y_1@}) \Rightarrow x_1={@x_1@}, &nbsp; y_1={@y_1@}\)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(B({@x_2@},{@y_2@}) \Rightarrow x_2={@x_2@}, &nbsp; y_2={@y_2@}\)</p>

<p>So, the distance between the two points is,</p>

<p hidden>{@simp:false@}</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\begin{align*}
|AB| &= {@line1@} \\
&={@line2@} \\
&={@line3@} \\
&={@ta1@}
\end{align*}\)</p>
<p hidden>{@simp:true@}</p>

<p>Therefore, \( |AB| = {@ta1@} \)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
